 Exercise: Transcripts and genes
The GTF file is sorted: all entries from the first line of the table, until you again see ‚Äúgene‚Äù in the third column, belong to the first gene. Can you make sense of all these entries for this gene, given what you know of gene structures? How many transcripts does this gene have?


(Click to see some pointers)


The first gene (‚ÄúLOC120427725‚Äù) has 3 transcripts.
Each transcript has 6-7 exons, 5 CDSs, and a start and stop codon.

